prompt:
Add a public function called UnwrapOrDefault to Calculator.calr that unwraps an Option<i32> or returns a default value. It takes Option<i32> parameter opt and i32 parameter defaultVal and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor Option matching syntax:
§F{f003:UnwrapOrDefault:pub}
  §I{Option<i32>:opt}
  §I{i32:defaultVal}
  §O{i32}
  §R §W{w001} opt
    §K §SM §VAR{v} → v
    §K §NN → defaultVal
  §/W{w001}
§/F{f003}

The Option pattern matching syntax:
- §SM §VAR{v} matches Some and binds the inner value to v
- §NN matches None
- Use these with §K in a switch expression
- §R §W{...} returns the result of the switch expression
